w, including Apple&#39;s. We also like its foldable design, which will allow it to fit better in cramped spaces and in travel bags.</p><h2> Anker PowerCore 26,800 </h2><p><core-commerce id="d3b564e299a24d77931e7fe852ccf16f" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> It&#39;s smart to have a portable battery with you when you&#39;re using your iPad on the go – regardless of if it&#39;s your daily driver or you&#39;re only using it for a few select tasks. <a data-i13n="cpos:24;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfAP4frCSWpQqpijLBMO6_wEwwDt_g_nEekuQIjSBa6J&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FAnker-PowerCore-Portable-Double-Speed-Recharging%2Fdp%2FB01JIWQPMW">Anker&#39;s PowerCore 26,800</a> has a high enough capacity to charge up most tablets almost two times over, making it very unlikely that you&#39;ll totally run out of power before you get to your next destination. While it won&#39;t charge laptops, it will work for most mobile devices, and it has three USB-A ports so you can power up to three devices simultaneously. And since the brick itself weighs just over one pound, it won&#39;t weigh down your bag all day long, either.</p><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-ipad-accessories-130018595.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-ipad-accessories-130018595.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 94f7e0a4-2c37-37fd-9879-739177ccbf4c</guid><dc:creator> Valentina Palladino</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 04 Jul 2023 14:30:18 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688481019</ingested><modified> 2023-07-04T14:30:35+00:00 </modifi